Durrandon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Successor</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Qarlton_III_Durrandon\" title=\"Qarlton III Durrandon\">Qarlton III Durrandon</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">Personal Information</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nQarlton the Conqueror</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">Family</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Dynasty</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">House Durrandon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Qarlton_III_Durrandon\" title=\"Qarlton III Durrandon\">Qarlton III Durrandon</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">References</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Qarlton II Durrandon</b>, self-styled <b>Qarlton the Conqueror</b>, was a <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_King\" title=\"Storm King\">Storm King</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">House Durrandon</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Andal_invasion\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Andal invasion\">Andal invasion</a> and a grandson of King <a href=\"/index.php/Erich_VII_Durrandon\" title=\"Erich VII Durrandon\">Erich VII Durrandon</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Qarlton_II_Durrandon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Qarlton was the first Storm King to face the <a href=\"/index.php/Andals\" title=\"Andals\">Andals</a> in battle. He also, after four generations of war, completed the reconquest  of <a href=\"/index.php/Massey%27s_Hook\" title=\"Massey&#39;s Hook\">Massey's Hook</a> after a year's siege and slaying the last <a href=\"/index.php/House_Massey\" title=\"House Massey\">Massey</a> king, <a href=\"/index.php/Josua_Massey\" title=\"Josua Massey\">Josua</a>. However, he held his conquest for less than two years, as <a href=\"/index.php/Togarion_Bar_Emmon\" title=\"Togarion Bar Emmon\">Togarion Bar Emmon</a> threw the stormlanders away from Massey's Hook. Qarlton II, however, soon had to face the Andals, whose longships had begun to land on the Stormlands' shores. Qarlton II was succeeded by <a href=\"/index.php/Qarlton_III_Durrandon\" title=\"Qarlton III Durrandon\">Qarlton III Durrandon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Qarlton_II_Durrandon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Erich_VII_Durrandon\" title=\"Erich VII Durrandon\">Erich VII</a></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2